16/05/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Three people were killed and seven were wounded by a knife-wielding man in a village near the central town of Visoko on Saturday (May 15th).
Four of the injured are very young children.
Police say that according to preliminary information, the alleged attacker, as Nedim Fejzic, 40, has a history of mental illness and that he has attacked with a knife before.
New to the village, he did not know the victims and was apparently under the influence of alcohol during the killing spree.
(Reuters, AFP, Radio Sarajevo, B92, Beta, FTV, Nezavisne Novine - 15/05/10)
